      "category": "Discovery & Documentation",
      "category_id": "DISC",
      "title": "No automated breaking-change detection in CI",
      "description": "tqdm uses semantic versioning via setuptools-scm. The public API is defined in tqdm/__init__.py via __all__. Deprecation warnings exist for features slated for removal in v5.0.0. However, no automated breaking-change detection exists in CI — no typed-export diff tool, no schema comparison step, no consumer-driven contract testing.",
      "gap": "No automated breaking-change detection in the CI pipeline. API contract stability relies on manual review and deprecation warnings rather than tooling.",
      "recommendation": "Add a CI step that compares the public API surface (exports in __init__.py, function signatures in std.py) between the PR branch and the base branch, flagging removals or signature changes as breaking.",
      "severity": "Medium",
      "priority": "P2",
      "effort": "Medium",
      "phase": 2,
      "evidence": {
        "file": "pyproject.toml",
        "lines": null
      },
      "ara_metadata": {
